reviewText: There was some concern that this DVD may not be in widesreen format but it cetainly is. Both movies are in beautful 1.85:1 aspect ratio. They both have a lot of extras and it seems the original 1983 Vacation here has all of the features of the Special Edition  PLUS European Vacation as a bonus for the same price? Even though European Vacation is really an inferior sequel, why not have it if you get for free?

reviewText: I'm so glad that these two films are being sold together. I love each of them. These are definitely the kind of movies you never get tired of seeing, I've seen both of them enough to know. It's unusual for a sequel to be as good as the original but in my opinion European Vacation is just as good as Family Vacation, in some ways maybe better. These films don't try to be something they're not. They are just plain and simple laugh out loud funny. When you have all the jokes and gags memorized and they can still make you laugh, that's really saying something. There are also some great commentaries included featuring Chevy Chase.Jennifer K. LaffertyAuthor of Offbeat Love Stories and More
